fields.name: Kanye West - College Drop Out
fields.description: The College Dropout is the debut studio hip-hop album by American rapper and producer Kanye West. It was released on February 10, 2004, by Roc-A-Fella Records and Def Jam Recordings.

fields.name: MF DOOM - MM..Food
fields.description: Mm..Food (stylized in all caps) is the fifth studio hip-hop album by British-American rapper/producer MF Doom, released by Rhymesayers in November 2004.

fields.name: Mac Miller - Circles
fields.description: Circles is the sixth and final studio album by American rapper, singer and hip-hop artist Mac Miller. It was released posthumously on January 17, 2020, by REMember Music and Warner Records, and was being worked on by Miller before his death in September 2018. Production was completed by Jon Brion.

fields.name: Freddie Gibbs - Alfredo
fields.description: Alfredo is a collaborative studio hip-hop album by American rapper Freddie Gibbs and American hip hop producer The Alchemist. It was released on May 29, 2020, through Gibbs' own record label ESGN Records, as well as ALC Records and Empire Distribution.

fields.name: The XX - XX
fields.description: xx is the debut album by English indie pop band the xx. It was released on 14 August 2009 by Young Turks, an imprint label of XL Recordings. After signing a record contract with XL, the xx recorded the album from December 2008 to February 2009 at the label's in-house studio in London.

fields.name: Bombay Bicycle Club - Everything Else Has Gone Wrong
fields.description: Everything Else Has Gone Wrong is the fifth studio album by the British indie rock band Bombay Bicycle Club. It was released on 17 January 2020 by the band's own Mmm... Records imprint of Island Records, Caroline International and Arts & Crafts.

fields.name: Lucky Daye - Painted
fields.description: Painted is the debut studio album by American indie singer Lucky Daye. It was released on May 24, 2019, by Keep Cool Records and RCA Records.

fields.name: LCD Soundsystem - Sound of Silver
fields.description: Sound of Silver is the second studio album by American indie rock band LCD Soundsystem. The album was released jointly through DFA and Capitol Records in the United States and EMI elsewhere, first on March 12, 2007, in the United Kingdom.

fields.name: Miles Davis - Kind of Blue
fields.description: Kind of Blue is a studio album by American jazz trumpeter-composer Miles Davis. It was recorded on March 2 and April 22, 1959, at Columbia's 30th Street Studio in New York City, and released on August 17 of that year by Columbia Records.

fields.name: John Coltrane - Giant Steps
fields.description: Giant Steps is the fifth studio album by jazz musician John Coltrane as leader. It was released in February 1960 on Atlantic Records.

fields.name: Gil Scott Heron - Pieces of a Man
fields.description: Pieces of a Man is the first studio album by American soul, funk and jazz vocalist Gil Scott-Heron. It was recorded in April 1971 at RCA Studios in New York City and released later that year by Flying Dutchman Records.

fields.name: Roy Ayers - Everybody Loves the Sunshine
fields.description: Everybody Loves the Sunshine is a studio album by soul artist Roy Ayers released under the Roy Ayers Ubiquity umbrella. It was released through Polydor Records in 1976. It peaked at number 51 on the Billboard 200 chart.

fields.name: KRK Rokit RP8
fields.description: Redefining the industry level for studio monitors. The KRK RP8 G4 Studio Monitors are engineered to deliver the best listening experience possible. Boasting the same quality that made the previous generation so integral to your studio, the RP8 G4's still manage to work in new features. Matching Kevlar drivers ensure durability and unwavering quality, while a built-in LCD displays EQ information for incredible visualisation.

fields.name: Behringer
fields.description: The Behringer Studio 50USB Studio Monitors (Pair) are USB/Analogue high-resolution 2-Way Studio Monitors with Bi-Amplification.

fields.name: Yamaha HS5 MP Studio Monitors
fields.description: The Yamaha HS5 combines a wide range of premium-grade components including larger-than-normal magnets for optimal audio fidelity. The advanced magnetic field design ensures extreme accuracy when it comes to sound reproduction, paramount for mixing and mastering purposes. Its 2-way bi-amplified design is comprised of a 5-inch cone woofer and a 1-inch dome tweeter. The two components are powered separately by dedicated amplifiers for maximum efficiency. The woofer is driven a 45W amplifier, with the tweeter driven by a 25W amplifier. This ensures optimal audio performance even at higher sound levels.

fields.name: Audio Technica LP120
fields.description: The Audio Technica LP120USB is a sturdy player that not only plays records but can copy vinyl straight to your hard-drive.

fields.name: Reloop AMS-RP-4000-MK2
fields.description: Reloop may not be a name you’re familiar with, but its AMS-RP-4000-MK2 is an excellent entry-level option for aspiring DJs.

fields.name: Pioneer PLX1000 Direct Drive DJ Turntable
fields.description: The PLX-1000 is precision engineered for the booth. This high-torque direct drive professional turntable is equipped with a classic layout and a rubber-lined, S-shaped tone arm that improves isolation and prevents feedback. It is solidly built for excellent vibration damping and ultra-precise, high grade audio playback.

fields.name: Micro Fibre Brush
fields.description: he Monacor DC-100 Carbon Fibre LP Brush is the ultimate vinyl-care accessory for any record collector or owner. The DC-100 features more than one-million conducting fibres. These fibres are designed to discharge static charges and remove dust at the same time, maintaining the life of your precious record collection.
